# Sprint 1 — Auth frontend

## Purpose

Deliver the **unauthenticated** and **authenticated** UI shells for QuizMaker, wired to the backend auth contract (see API PRD). Forms follow **shadcn/ui** + **react-hook-form** + **Zod**; styling uses **Tailwind** utilities and `src/app/globals.css` only for global imports per project rules.

---

## Token handling (normative)

| Concern | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| **localStorage key** | `quizmaker_auth_token` — stores the JWT **access** string returned by login (or equivalent bearer token field name from the API contract). |
| **Write** | Set **only** after a **successful** `POST` login response that includes a token; optionally clear any stale value before write. |
| **Read** | On the **client**: before calling protected APIs; on **app load** for authenticated areas to decide whether to bootstrap `/me`. **Never** read this key in Server Components or route handlers for security-sensitive authorization (use middleware + server-verified session patterns in later sprints if moving to cookies). For Sprint 1, **client-side** guards and fetch wrappers read the key. |
| **Clear** | On **logout** (user action), on **401** from a protected call when refresh is not in scope, and before replacing with a new token on re-login if required by UX. |
| **`Authorization` header** | For client-side `fetch` to protected routes: `Authorization: Bearer <quizmaker_auth_token value>`. Centralize in a small helper (e.g. `src/lib/auth-client.ts` or `src/lib/services/auth-fetch.ts`) so all calls attach the header consistently. Server-side `fetch` from RSC must **not** use localStorage; Sprint 1 defers server-authenticated data loading to client bootstrap where needed. |

---

## Phase A — Routing, layouts, unauthenticated shell; redirect skeleton

### Goal

Establish **App Router** structure under `src/app/`, shared **unauthenticated** layout (marketing/auth shell), and a **middleware** (or equivalent) skeleton that defines **where** auth redirects will run—without requiring full JWT validation until Phase C–D.

### Tasks

- Add route groups or segments for `(auth)` (login/signup) vs `(app)` or `/(dashboard)` for post-login home, per final IA.
- Implement root `src/app/layout.tsx` composition: fonts/globals, providers if needed.
- Add `middleware.ts` at project root (Next convention) with **matchers** documented; initial behavior: static pass-through or redirect stubs (e.g. `/login` ↔ `/` rules TBD with Phase C).
- Unauthenticated shell: header/footer or minimal chrome using shadcn primitives.

### File-level touchpoints (approximate)

- `src/app/layout.tsx`
- `src/app/(auth)/layout.tsx` (or `src/app/login/layout.tsx`, etc.)
- `src/app/(auth)/login/page.tsx` — placeholder page
- `src/app/(auth)/signup/page.tsx` — placeholder page
- `middleware.ts`
- `src/app/globals.css` — ensure Tailwind entry only; no ad-hoc global CSS for auth beyond tokens/theme

### Acceptance criteria

- Navigating to `/login` and `/signup` renders inside the unauthenticated shell without errors.
- `middleware.ts` exists, exports `config.matcher`, and documents intended protected prefixes (even if logic is noop/stub).
- No `pages/` router usage.

### Backend contract dependencies

- None required to ship shell; optional **health** ping endpoint name only if used for “API up” badge: e.g. `GET /api/health` (if defined in API PRD).

